	<p>This paean to bread comes as the antithetical response to today's dietary climate of gluten intolerance. Since the genesis of agriculture, bread has been one of the most universal and significant forms of sustenance in Western Civilization. The band Bread, with all its love ballads, is astute in this practice, assuredly knowing that the etymology of <em>companion</em> literally means, <em>with bread</em>. Indeed, we all want companionship (note that this is not a boat of bread, however). Indeed, there is some bread digesting in my stomach as I write this. Come, let us sing its praise.
	</p>
	</section>
</article>
